Genitalia (
Fig. 6 D, E, F
): Eighth abdominal tergite simple and rectangular; caudal extension of valvae in lateral view approximately 2 / 3 length of valvae; valvae ventral keel as a blunt process pointing caudally (
Fig. 6 E
); penis long and uniformly narrow throughout, with a prominently convex anterior half, a shallowly concave posterior half; distal portion of penis possesses a single cornutus (
Fig. 6 F
). Saccus very elongated and triangular in shape.

Distribution. The species is known only from two localities in the Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta : Cuchilla de San Lorenzo and San Pedro in montane forest at 2200 m above sea level (
Fig. 7
). Adults have been captures from January and June.
